EU Stress Tests Use Spain Jobless Rate of 22%, Vanguardia Says

-- B y   E m m a   R o s s - T h o m a s
-- 
2011-03-10T07:18:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/eu-stress-tests-use-spain-jobless-rate-of-22-vanguardia-says.html
European stress tests on banks will
include a Spanish unemployment rate of more than 22 percent in
2012 in an “adverse” scenario, La Vanguardia reported, without
saying where it got the information.  The “adverse” Spanish scenario also includes negative
inflation and a 1.1 percent economic contraction in 2012, the
newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
